<item>
            <title>[JDK-8298472] AArch64: Detect Ampere-1 and Ampere-1A CPUs and set default options</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8298472</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Add CPU detection code for Ampere-1 and Ampere-1A CPUs, and configure default AArch64 options.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
processor       : 0&lt;br/&gt;
BogoMIPS        : &lt;br/&gt;
Features        : &lt;br/&gt;
CPU implementer : 0xc0&lt;br/&gt;
CPU architecture: 8&lt;br/&gt;
CPU variant     : 0x0&lt;br/&gt;
CPU part        : 0xac3&lt;br/&gt;
CPU revision    : 0&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
By the way, GCC has already had the changes to support Ampere-1 and Ampere-1A, &lt;a href=&quot;https://gcc.gnu.org/pipermail/gcc-patches/2022-November/605942.html&quot;&gt;https://gcc.gnu.org/pipermail/gcc-patches/2022-November/605942.html&lt;/a&gt;. So it is time to have similar detection and support in JDK as well.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Plan to backport to 17 once the MR gets approved to mainline.</description>
