                            <comment id="14551218" author="qpzhang" created="Sun, 15 Jan 2023 06:38:23 -0800"  >Fix Request (17u)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- Reason: This is to turn on UseSIMDForMemoryOps AArch64 option for Ampere-1 and Ampere-1A CPUs, for better performance on memory ops especially arrays. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- Risk: Low risk to other functions/systems due to the CPU detection logic, the impact is on Ampere-1 and Ampere-1A CPUs only. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- Testing: Besides pre-submit tests, we also covered performance measurement with micro benchmarks JTReg micro:java.lang.ArrayCopy*, and functionality check with tier1 tests on Ampere-1 system, and confirmed no new failure found. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- Notes: Not a clean backport, manually fixed the copyright years and some mismatched line numbers in source files. Please see details in the 17u PR#1067.</comment>
